sentences: Christina Petrowska Quilico  (born December 30, 1948) is a Canadian pianist.
She was appointed to the Order of Canada in 2020 “For her celebrated career as a classical and contemporary pianist and for championing Canadian music.”
In 2021, she was named a Fellow of the Royal Society of Canada.
Petrowska Quilico was born on December 30, 1948 in Ottawa, Ontario.
Barely four months after turning 14, she made her performance debut at The Town Hall in New York City (May 4, 1963).
Barely four months after turning 14, she made her performance debut at The Town Hall in New York City (May 4, 1963).
She later taught at The Royal Conservatory of Music, Carleton University and University of Ottawa before joining the faculty of music at York University in 1987.
In 1992, astronaut Steve MacLean brought her recording of Alexina Louie’s Star-Filled Night on his first mission to the Space Shuttle Columbia.
In 1992, astronaut Steve MacLean brought her recording of Alexina Louie’s Star-Filled Night on his first mission to the Space Shuttle Columbia.
In 2006, on board the Space Shuttle Atlantis, MacLean took the recording of her as soloist in the world premiere performance of David Mott's piano concerto Eclipse.
In 2007, Petrowska Quilico received the Friends of Canadian Music Award from the Canadian Music Centre and Canadian League of Composers.
In 2020, she was appointed as a member of the Order of Canada.
In May 2021, she was a winner of the York University Research Awards, and in September was named a Fellow of the Royal Society of Canada.
In May 2021, she was a winner of the York University Research Awards, and in September was named a Fellow of the Royal Society of Canada.
Quilico was married to composer Michel-Georges Brégent until he died in 1993.
She subsequently remarried, to baritone Louis Quilico, who died seven years later.
In his memory, she created The Christina and Louis Quilico Award, which is administered by the Ontario Arts Foundation and held every two years under the auspices of the Canadian Opera Company.
